---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Now: Michael Vivirito"
  description="What Michael Vivirito is focused on right now. SRE work, FreeBSD networking, NixOS, and the rest of the homelab."
  canonical="/now"
>

  <section>
    <header style="text-align: center; margin-bottom: 3rem;">
      <h1>Now</h1>
      <p class="text-muted">What I'm focused on right now.</p>
      <p class="text-muted" style="font-size: 0.875rem;">Last updated: June 13, 2026</p>
    </header>

    <div class="card" style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">

      <pre><code>$ cat ~/.status
Last updated: 2026-06-13
Location:  Los Angeles, CA</code></pre>

      <h2>Building</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong><a href="/openworld">OpenWorld</a></strong>: A coordination layer for civic action, pin a place, propose an idea, flag an issue, give kudos, or organize a time-bounded event. <strong>iOS and Android are live</strong> on the App Store and Google Play.</li>
        <li><strong>Team Brain &amp; Oncall Agent</strong> (work): a shared-memory knowledge layer that every team AI session consults automatically, killing the explanation tax for engineers and feeding the bot that comments on incoming tasks. Currently rolling out across the team. <a href="/resume#key-achievements">Full write-up on the resume</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Personal Second Brain Vault</strong>: an Obsidian-backed personal vault with a Telegram surface for capture and retrieval. Same instinct as the team brain at work, applied to my own daily memory loop. In the spirit of <a href="https://karpathy.ai" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Karpathy's</a> personal-system experiments.</li>
        <li><strong>FreeBSD pf router</strong>: a self-built edge router and firewall at the heart of my homelab. FreeBSD 15 on a CWWK N100 mini PC (hostname <code>homefw</code>), with an X-ONU-SFPP XGS-PON SFP+ module replacing the AT&amp;T fiber gateway entirely. ZFS root, pf, unbound, ISC DHCP, WireGuard, and a <a href="/go/sodola-10g/" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Sodola 12-port 10G managed switch</a> downstream of the LAN trunk. <a href="/homelab">Tour the setup</a>.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Running</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>FreeBSD 15 edge router (<code>homefw</code>) behind XGS-PON, with pf, unbound, ISC dhcpd, ntpd</li>
        <li>NixOS on Proxmox for declarative server management</li>
        <li>Monitoring: Prometheus, Grafana, Alertmanager</li>
        <li>WireGuard for road-warrior VPN back into the LAN</li>
        <li>ZFS everywhere with hourly snapshots and offsite send/recv</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Learning</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>MCP server design patterns and agent workflow primitives</li>
        <li>Obsidian + Telegram automation for the personal second brain</li>
        <li>bhyve internals</li>
        <li>IPv6 design for residential networks (real prefix delegation, not 6to4)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Writing About</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>FreeBSD pf router build and operations</li>
        <li>pf.conf design: rules, NAT, anti-spoofing, logging</li>
        <li>Team-brain architecture and the &ldquo;explanation tax&rdquo; framing</li>
        <li>AWS cost optimization (real numbers, not fluff)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Stack</h2>
      <pre><code>$ cat ~/.stack
Edge:       FreeBSD 15 (homefw) + pf + unbound + XGS-PON SFP
Servers:    NixOS 24.11 (declarative)
Hypervisor: Proxmox + ZFS
Local AI:   Ollama on Threadripper 1950X + RTX 4080 (NixOS VM, GPU passthrough)
Editor:     Neovim
Shell:      Zsh + Starship
Terminal:   Alacritty
Monitoring: Prometheus + Grafana
PKM:        Obsidian + Telegram (personal vault)</code></pre>

      <h2>Reading</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Re-reading <em>The Design and Implementation of the FreeBSD Operating System</em> end to end</li>
        <li>Working through <em>Designing Data-Intensive Applications</em> patterns in production</li>
        <li>Following NixOS RFCs and the Lix project</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Not Doing</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Social media (mostly)</li>
        <li>Chasing every new framework</li>
        <li>Premature optimization</li>
      </ul>

      <pre><code>$ echo "Ship fast. Ship often. Ship boring."</code></pre>

    </div>

    <div style="max-width: 800px; margin: 2rem auto 0; text-align: center;">
      <p class="text-muted">
        Inspired by <a href="https://sive.rs/nowff" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Derek Sivers' /now page movement</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-secondary">← Home</a>
        <a href="/#blog" class="btn btn-secondary">Blog</a>
        <a href="contact" class="btn btn-primary">Get in Touch</a>
      </p>
    </div>

  </section>

</BaseLayout>
